author: Spencer Jakab
title: Natural-Gas Glut Keeps Pressure on Prices
text:
As campaign slogans go, “Drill, baby, drill” is starting to sound as quaint as Barack Obama’s “Yes we can!” or Jimmy Carter’s “Not just peanuts.”
A big reason is that a barrel of crude only fetches peanuts these days at less than half the peak of summer 2014. But oil is still black gold compared with U.S. natural gas.
